        <p>In the diagram, all masses and angle \(\theta\) are given. The pulleys and the string are ideal. The tension of the top string is \(T_1\) and the tension of the bottom string is \(T_2\). Frictional forces are negligible.</p><br/><img src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/BK/BK27.png" alt="p1a" texwrap="none" align="top"/><br/><u><b>Part1:</b></u>What is the correct relationship between the magnitudes of the accelerations of blocks 1 and 2?

      <br/>
